ign==\n*[[Umbra (company)]]\n\n==Book stores==\n{{See also|List of independent bookstores}}\n\n*[[Aqua Books]] in [[Winnipeg|Winnipeg, Manitoba]] (defunct)\n*[[Attic Books]] in [[London, Ontario]]\n*[[Bakka-Phoenix]] in [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]]\n*[[Bison Books]] in Winnipeg, Manitoba\n*[[Book City (Canada)|Book City]] in Toronto, Ontario\n*Book Outlet Retail Store in [[St. Catharines, Ontario]]\n*The Bookshelf in [[Guelph, Ontario]] est. 1973\n*[[The Book Room]] in [[Halifax, Nova Scotia]] was, at the time of its 2008 closing, the oldest bookstore in Canada (defunct)\n*[[Camas Bookstore and Infoshop]] in [[Victoria, British Columbia]]\n*[[Glad Day Bookshop]] in Toronto, Ontario\n*[[Highway Book Shop]] near [[Cobalt, Ontario]] (defunct)\n*[[Hyman's Book and Art Shoppe]], an independent [[History of the Jews in Canada|Jewish]] bookstore in Toronto, Ontario (defunct)\n*[[Indigo Books and Music]], Canada's largest bookstore chain, based in [[Toronto]]\n*[[Insoumise bookstore]], independent [[Anarchism|anarchist]] bookstore in [[Montreal]]\n*[[Librairie Raffin]], small independently run chain located in [[Quebec]] and specializing in [[French language]] books\n*[[Little Sister's Book and Art Emporium]] in [[Vancouver|Vancouver, British Columbia]]\n*[[McNally Robinson]], small independently run chain of stores across Canada\n*[[Mondragon Bookstore & Coffeehouse]] in Winnipeg, Manitoba (defunct)\n*[[The Monkey's Paw (bookstore)|The Monkey's Paw]] in Toronto, Ontario\n*[[Munro's Books]] in Victoria, British Columbia\n*[http://www.novelideabooks.ca Novel Idea] in Kingston, Ontario\n*[[Spartacus Books]] in Vancouver, British Columbia\n*[[This Ain't the Rosedale Library]] in Toronto, Ontario (defunct)\n*[[Toronto Women's Bookstore]] in Toronto, Ontario (defunct)\n*[[The Word Bookstore]] in Montreal\n\n==Clothing stores==\n{{See also|List_of_Canadian_clothing_store_chains}}\n*[[Harry Rosen Inc.]]\n\n*[[Le Chateau]]\n*[[Lululemon]]\n*[[Mark's]]\n*[[Moores]]\n*[[Roots Canada]