eters long and located on the Tallet. On the top of the tower sits a statue of Saint Georges, the intercessor of the Tallet. The statue was placed there by the Lebanese Army on 30 December 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nna-leb.gov.lb/ar/show-news/198818/|title=\u0627\u0631\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u062d\u062a\u0641\u0644\u062a \u0628\u0631\u0641\u0639 \u062a\u0645\u062b\u0627\u0644 \u0645\u0627\u0631 \u062c\u0631\u062c\u0633 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0628\u0631\u062c\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064a\u0627\u062d\u064a|first=\u0627\u0644\u0648\u0643\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a\u0629|last=\u0644\u0644\u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645|website=\u0627\u0644\u0648\u0643\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645}}</ref> The statue can be seen from sky at night (due to its unique lightning) and remains the only building with that perk.\n\n*'''Waterland''': Waterland is a summer resort and hotel. It has been found in 2010. This resort attracts many visitors from nearby villages.\n\n==Harf Ardeh==\n\nA small village that is a significant part of Ardeh community that shares some of the families with Ardeh. The number of registered in this community has increased significantly in the past 4 decades because many persons moved in from the District of Dannieh. In 1998 there were 1220 registered persons (963 registered in 1988), 30% of them are emigrants. Haref Ardeh is a small village that is enriched with lot of social activities that distinguishes it with all its surroundings  and well known by its scouts organization and its music band as well as many other sports and religious organizations.\n\n==Agriculture==\n\nOlives, oranges, grapes, tobacco, fruits and vegetables are grown in the area.\n\n==Water sources==\n\n*El Kadi spring\n*Ain Ardeh\n\n==Religious aspect==\nArdeh is considered to have a very religious community, like every Lebanese countryside. This parish follows the western christian calendar and it is under the sovereignty of the Maronite Archdiocese of Tripoli. Currently, the head of the parish is the auxilliary bishop Monseigneur Boutrous Jabbour. In his time, the church of Mary has been built and the church of Saint Georges has been refurbished.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://forzgharta.com/%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%ae%d9%88%d8%b1%d8%a3%d8%b3%d9%82%d9%81-%d8%a8%d8%b7%d8%b1%d8%b3-%d8%ac%d8%a8%d9%88%d8%b1/|title=\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0648\u0631\u0623\u0633\u0642\u0641 \u0628\u0637\u0631\u0633 \u062c\u0628\u0648\u0631|date=March 6, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, Monseigneur Jabbour celebrated his 60th year as a priest,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://safiralchamal.com/2018/10/14/%d8%a7%d8%a8%d8%b1%d8%b4%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%b7%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%a8%d9%84%d8%b3-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%a7%d8%b1%d9%88%d9%86%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%aa%d9%83%d8%b1%d9%85-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%ae%d9%88%d8%b1%d8%a7%d8%b3/|title=\u0627\u0628\u0631\u0634\u064a\u0629 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u0643\u0631\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0648\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0642\u0641 \u0628\u0637\u0631\u0633 \u062c\u0628\u0648\u0631}}</ref> which he spent all of them in the parish of Ardeh.\n\nArdeh celebrates the following religious days:\n*[[Saint Charbel]]-Haref Ardeh on every second Sunday of July\n*[[John the Apostle|Saint John]]-Haref Ardeh on December 27\n*[[Saint Rita]]-Haref Ardeh on May 22\n*[[Saint Georges]]-Mar jirjis on April 23\n*[[Simeon Stylites|Saint Simon of the Stylite]]-Mar Semaan on September 1\n*Saints [[Saint Sarkis|Sarkis]] and [[Saint Bakchos|Bakhos]] on October 7\n*[[Virgin mary|Virgin Mary]] Festival on August 15\n*[[Christmas Day]] On December 25\n*[[Easter]] Depends on the Western Christian Calendar\n\n==Useful information==\n\n===Education===\n\nThe school in Ardeh was present before World War I and teaching was done by the priests. Among them were Wakim Fadlallah, Youssef Chedid and Elias Awkar.\n\nNowadays, there are 2 schools in Ardeh, one is private and the other is public. The private school was founded in the 1930's by the Lazarists and in 1947, the school became sponsored by the Maronite Archdiocese and still is until this day. In 2006, the maronite school had 219 registered students.<ref name=\"auto\"/> The public school was founded in the 1960 by the Lebanese government and it had 255 registered student in 2006.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n===Families===\n*Al-Abboud\n*Akari\n*Amine\n*Aoun\n*Arab\n*Assaf\n*Ayash\n*Azar\n*Badawi\n*Badra\n*Bechara\n*Bou Dib\n*Bou Francis\n*Bou Nassif\n*Boulos\n*Bourji\n*Chahine\n*Chahoud\n*Chami\n*Chedid\n*Dib\n*Doumit\n*Eid\n*Francis\n*Fadlallah\n*Farah\n*Ghaleb\n*Hadidi\n*Hajj\n*Hanna\n*Haykal\n*Helou\n*Jabbour\n*Jneid\n*Kanaan\n*Kamel\n*Khattar\n*Khoury\n*Lattouf\n*Maatouk\n*Mahfoud\n*Mardini\n*Marroun\n*Mazraani\n*Moawad\n*Moukhtafi\n*Naoum\n*Nassour\n*Nassif\n*Nouhra\n*Rawda\n*Rezzi\n*Saab\n*Saad\n*Sadek\n*Saghir\n*Saliba\n*Tadros\n*Tawni\n*Trad\n*Yarak\n*Younes\n*Wehbe\n\n===Administration===\nThe municipality of 15 members is shared with Harf Ardeh and two small communities Beit Awkar and Beit Obeid. The seats are distributed according to the number of listed voters: Ardeh 9 seats, Harf Ardeh 4 seats, Beit Awkar 1 seat, Beit Obeid 1 seat.\n\nThe current members of the board of municipality are:<ref>http://elections.gov.lb/getattachment/4798476d-5c99-4a56-8e3d-0f85b4b60a0e/%D8%B2%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%A7.aspx</ref>\n\n*Habib Lattouf (President)\n*Elie Hosny (Vice President)\n*Raymond Marroun\n*Ibrahim Jabbour\n*Ghassan Haykal\n*Sayed Moukhtafi\n*Georgette Maatouk\n*Sandra Fadlallah\n*Bedouin Al Tawni\n*Semaan Dib\n*Bakhos Bou Francis\n*Elie Mardini\n*Francis Bou Francis\n*Abdallah Obeid\n*Elias Awkar\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.localiban.org/article3606.html  Ardeh - Harf Ardeh - Beit Okar - Beit Abid], Localiban\n*[https://www.ehdenfamilytree.com/ Ehden Family Tree]\n\n{{Zgharta District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in the North Governorate]]\n[[Category:Zgharta District]]\n[[Category:Maronite Christian communities in Lebanon]]\n\n\n{{lebanon-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Maroun1899", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReligious aspect", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ardeh,_Lebanon"}
{"title_page": "Stephen West (designer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist\n| name = Stephen West\n| birth_place = [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Illinois]], [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]\n| website = [https://www.westknits.com Westknits.com]\n}}'''Stephen West''' is an American [[knitting|knitter]], [[fashion designer]], educator, and author. His shawl designs and innovative use of color have helped him become an internationally recognized and respected designer. \nHe began to publish his own patterns in 2009 on sites like [[Knitty]]<ref name=\"knitty\">{{Cite magazine |last=West |first=Stephen |date=2009 |title=Colonnade shawl - Knitty: Fall 2009 |url=https://knitty.com/ISSUEfall09/PATTcolonnade.php |magazine=[[Knitty]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and [[Ravelry]],<ref name=\"ravelry\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ravelry.com/designers/stephen-west |title=Ravelry: Designs by Stephen West |website=www.ravelry.com |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> He was inspired to start designing by the creative atmosphere at his local yarn store in Urbana.\nWest has gone on to publish a series of pattern books under his design brand '''Westknits'''. His simple, clean, architectural designs have now been knitted by thousands of knitters all around the world. \n\nStephen has taught workshops throughout the United States and internationally in Finland, Denmark, Germany, Italy, France, Israel, Iceland, UK. He also co-owns the yarn boutique Stephen & Penelope in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]], and in 2019 he launched a yarn brand called '''West Wool''' with his business partner Malia Mae Joseph.<ref name=\"westknits\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.westknits.com/ |title=Westknits |website=Westknits |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nBorn in [[Tulsa]], [[Oklahoma]], West moved to [[Chicago]] as a teenager.<ref name=\"abc\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-09-17/men-who-unpick-knitting-stereoptype/11516016 |title='I pretended to be buying for my mum': Meet the men unpicking knitting's ultimate stereotype |last=Floris |first=Lise |date=2019-09-17 |website=ABC News |language=en-AU |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> A trained dancer, he studied dance at the [[University of Illinois]] Department of Dance.<ref name=\"ng\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/knit-the-big-time-stephen-west/article_edeb64ee-3e13-5f76-bc8e-4bf40c132149.html |title=Knit the big time: Stephen West |last=Merli |first=Melissa |date=2017-03-26 |website=The News-Gazette |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> While in school he learned to knit and enjoyed it greatly. He later recalled, \"I could always be found knitting between rehearsals, back stage and in between classes.\"<ref name=\"abc\" /> West then moved to Amsterdam to pursue a degree in [[choreography]] from the School for New Dance Development at the [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]. While there, he continued knitting and creating patterns, acquiring more recognition for his designs.<ref name=\"ng\" /> \n\nWest regularly publishes patterns, leads knit-alongs, and shares photos on his Westknits Instagram, which had over 174 thousand followers as of April 2020.<ref name=\"insta\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/westknits/ |title=Stephen West (@westknits) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos |website=www.instagram.com |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> He is also known for his sense of humor, eccentric clothing,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://laughingsquid.com/how-to-transform-woolly-sweaters-into-sassy-pants-called-swants/ |title=How to Transform Woolly Sweaters Into Sassy Pants Called 'Swants' |last=Page |first=Justin |date=2013-11-08 |website=Laughing Squid |language=en-US |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and creatively choreographed knitting-themed music videos.<ref name=\"at\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.apartmenttherapy.com/should-we-be-wearing-more-shawls-12-questions-for-knitter-designer-stephen-west-242489 |title=Should We Be Wearing More Shawls? 17 Questions for Knitter-Designer Stephen West |last=Zimmerman |first=Edith |date=2017-03-27 |website=[[Apartment Therapy]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> \n\n==Works==\n* ''Westknits at Home'' (2014) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985299057}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 1: Shawls'' (2016) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131753}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 2: Sweaters'' (2017) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131777}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 3: Shawl Evolution''\n* ''Hiberknitting'' (2019) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131791}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:West, Stephen}}\n[[Category:University of Illinois alumni]]\n[[Category:People in knitting]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American textile artists]]\n[[Category:Writers from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Writers from Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:American choreographers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist\n| name = \n| birth_place = [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Illinois]], [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]\n| website = [https://www.westknits.com Westknits.com]\n}}'''Stephen West''' is an American [[knitting|knitter]], [[fashion designer]], educator, and author. His shawl designs and innovative use of color have helped him become an internationally recognized and respected designer. \nAfter beginning to publish his own patterns in 2009 on sites like [[Knitty]]<ref name=\"knitty\">{{Cite magazine |last=West |first=Stephen |date=2009 |title=Colonnade shawl - Knitty: Fall 2009 |url=https://knitty.com/ISSUEfall09/PATTcolonnade.php |magazine=[[Knitty]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and [[Ravelry]],<ref name=\"ravelry\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ravelry.com/designers/stephen-west |title=Ravelry: Designs by Stephen West |website=www.ravelry.com |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> West has also published a series of patterm books under his design brand '''Westknits'''. His simple, clean, architectural designs have been knitted by thousands of knitters all around the world. Stephen has taught workshops throughout the United States and internationally in Finland, Denmark, Germany, Italy, France, Israel, Iceland, UK. He also co-owns the yarn boutique Stephen & Penelope in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]], and in 2019 he launched a yarn brand called '''West Wool''' with his business partner Malia Mae Joseph.<ref name=\"westknits\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.westknits.com/ |title=Westknits |website=Westknits |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nBorn in [[Tulsa]], [[Oklahoma]], West moved to [[Chicago]] as a teenager.<ref name=\"abc\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-09-17/men-who-unpick-knitting-stereoptype/11516016 |title='I pretended to be buying for my mum': Meet the men unpicking knitting's ultimate stereotype |last=Floris |first=Lise |date=2019-09-17 |website=ABC News |language=en-AU |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> A trained dancer, he studied dance at the [[University of Illinois]] Department of Dance.<ref name=\"ng\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/knit-the-big-time-stephen-west/article_edeb64ee-3e13-5f76-bc8e-4bf40c132149.html |title=Knit the big time: Stephen West |last=Merli |first=Melissa |date=2017-03-26 |website=The News-Gazette |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> While in school he learned to knit and enjoyed it greatly. He later recalled, \"I could always be found knitting between rehearsals, back stage and in between classes.\"<ref name=\"abc\" /> West then moved to Amsterdam to pursue a degree in [[choreography]] from the School for New Dance Development at the [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]. While there, he continued knitting and creating patterns, acquiring more recognition for his designs.<ref name=\"ng\" /> \n\nWest regularly publishes patterns, leads knit-alongs, and shares photos on his Westknits Instagram, which had over 174 thousand followers as of April 2020.<ref name=\"insta\">{